,Recommended,415400,30673509,Posted: 22 March,all,Optimist Prime (the Gray),"A decent puzzle game that is similar in style to Sudoku, in that you are given a set of numbers and must ensure each row and column contain one of each number. The puzzles vary in size, up to 9x9, but are not as complicated as Sudoku puzzles (those which also require you to complete nine individual boxes of 1-9, in addition to rows and columns).As a simplified Sudoku game, each level is generally quick to solve. With a total of 64 puzzles, it likely won't take more than a few hours to complete the game. But the replay value is the same as any Sudoku or similarly-styled number game.The game allows you to lock in numbers that you're certain are correct, but locking-in numbers isn't required to complete the puzzles. This game could be improved with a couple small QOL features such as the ability to save your progress on a partially-completed level, and the ability to strike-out numbers on individual tiles that you've deemed to be incorrect... but overall I'd say this game is worth the $3 price tag, and very much worth a buy if on sale.Pros:- entertaining puzzle game- works as it is intended with no bugs encountered.- small price tag, and does go on sale (currently 45% Off, as of writing this review- I felt the colors worked well. They are neutral and calming yet still colorful; a good combination for a puzzle game.I wouldn't classify these as cons, but.. as far as puzzle games go, it's not riveting or groundbreaking and there's no wow-factor.All in all, I'd say a solid 8/10."
