,Not Recommended,415400,20632430,"Posted: 19 January, 2016",all,hisserbee,"I got this game to continue my puzzle binge after coming off of Hexcells and SquareCells. It's an okay variation of Sudoku. Kind of boring and really repetitive, especially because the difficulty doesn't vary much, but if you really love Sudoku you might like this too.I wasn't expecting much, but there was one serious flaw that turned this from a mediocre puzzle game to a truly frustrating exercise. There is NO WAY to mark that you have eliminated a number as a possibility in a given square. You can only mark that a square is 'locked' to a particular number. This means that you end up having to reexamine the same numbers in the same squares over and over to eliminate possibilites that you already eliminated. It mostly just made me want to play a real Sudoku game where you can do whatever you want with the pencil marks."
